Authors:
Weilun Sun
Alex Hall

Option Features & Command Line Suggestions

========== Bump Mapping ==========
Description:
A procedurally generated bump map.

Command Line Arguments:
-ka 0.3, 0.1, 0.1 -kd 0.0, 0.5, 0.0 -ks 0.4, 0.4, 0.4 -sp 10 -pl 4 4 4 1 1 1 -bump

========== Toon Shading ==========
Descrpition
A simple implementation of toon shading

Command Line Arguments
-ka 0.1, 0.1, 0.3 -kd 0.0, 0.0, 0.5 -ks 0.4, 0.4, 0.4 -sp 10 -pl 2 2 4 1 1 1 -toon

========== Other Shapes ==========
Description:
Switch between:
1. Cylinder
2. Torus
3. Tetrahedron
4. Torus Plane

Command Line Arguments
-ka 0.1, 0.1, 0.3 -kd 0.0, 0.0, 0.5 -ks 0.4, 0.4, 0.4 -sp 10 -pl 2 2 4 1 1 1 -shape 1

*Use mouse to rotate the cone.

-ka 0.1, 0.1, 0.3 -kd 0.0, 0.0, 0.5 -ks 0.4, 0.4, 0.4 -sp 10 -pl 2 2 4 1 1 1 -shape 2

-ka 0.1, 0.1, 0.3 -kd 0.0, 0.0, 0.5 -ks 0.4, 0.4, 0.4 -sp 10 -pl 2 2 4 1 1 1 -shape 3

-ka 0.1, 0.1, 0.3 -kd 0.0, 0.0, 0.5 -ks 0.4, 0.4, 0.4 -sp 10 -pl 2 2 4 1 1 1 -shape 4

========== Shadow Map ==========
Descrpition: The floating Torus will cast a shadow on the plane beneath it. This method uses a shadow map to generate a texture for the plane.

-ka 0.1, 0.1, 0.3 -kd 0.0, 0.0, 0.5 -ks 0.4, 0.4, 0.4 -sp 10 -pl 2 2 4 1 1 1 -shape 4
